## Analysis and Description of the Main Target Image:

The main target image displays two distinct structures made of building blocks.

**Structure 1 (Left Structure):**
- **Count & Layers:** This structure is taller and composed of 7 blocks arranged in 7 layers.
    - Layer 1 (Bottom): 1 Yellow rectangular block (horizontal orientation).
    - Layer 2: 1 Blue rectangular block (horizontal orientation), placed on top of the yellow block.
    - Layer 3: 1 Red U-shaped block, placed on top of the blue block.
    - Layer 4: 1 Orange cylindrical block, placed vertically on top of the red U-shaped block.
    - Layer 5: 1 Red U-shaped block, placed vertically on top of the orange cylinder.
    - Layer 6: 1 Yellow semi-circular block, placed on the top of the red U-shaped block on the left side.
    - Layer 7: 1 Yellow semi-circular block, placed on the top of the red U-shaped block on the right side.
- **Spatial Relationships:** The structure is built vertically layer by layer. The base is a yellow rectangle, followed by a blue rectangle. A red U-shape sits on top, followed by a vertical orange cylinder and another vertical red U-shape. Two yellow semi-circular blocks are placed side-by-side on the topmost red U-shape.

**Structure 2 (Right Structure):**
- **Count & Layers:** This structure is wider and composed of 7 blocks arranged in 7 layers (in terms of stacking height, although some blocks are placed side by side).
    - Layer 1 (Bottom): 1 Yellow rectangular block (horizontal orientation).
    - Layer 2: 1 Red U-shaped block, placed on top of the yellow block.
    - Layer 3: 1 Green rectangular block (horizontal orientation), placed on top of the red U-shaped block.
    - Layer 4: 1 Blue cubic block, placed on the left side on top of the green rectangular block.
    - Layer 5: 1 Blue cubic block, placed on the right side on top of the green rectangular block, adjacent to the first blue cube.
    - Layer 6: 1 Orange triangular block (leaning inwards to the left), placed on the right side at the base level, next to the yellow rectangular block.
    - Layer 7: 1 Orange triangular block (leaning inwards to the right), placed on the left side at the base level, next to the yellow rectangular block.
- **Spatial Relationships:** The structure starts with a yellow rectangular base, followed by a red U-shape and a green rectangle. Two blue cubes are placed side-by-side on top of the green rectangle. Two orange triangular blocks are placed on the ground level beside the base of the structure, one on each side and leaning inwards.

- Layer 5: Block index 1 (Red U-shape)

- Layer 7: Block index 11 (Yellow semi-circle)

**For Structure 2:**
- Layer 1: Block index 7 (Yellow horizontal rectangle)

- Layer 6: Block index 15 (Orange triangle leaning inwards to the left)
- Layer 7: Block index 16 (Orange triangle leaning inwards to the right)

**List of Block Indices:**
For Structure 1: 7, 5, 1, 9, 1, 11, 11
For Structure 2: 7, 1, 6, 3, 3, 15, 16
